Create python Virtual environment

pip install virtualenv

#Create virtual env of name ankit, it will create directoy as of same python interpreter in system
virtualenv ankit

# Goto ankit directory and run

Scripts/activate

#It will activate the virtualenv ,

 IN case of error.

#Open powershell in admin mmode and run
set-executiopolicy remotesigned
Y

#Now you can open python in this virtual env


###If you want to =be created this env same as system than use below flag
# Goto virtualenv directory and run
virtualenv --system-site-package  ankit2

#### Create requirement files in current env
pip freeze > requirements.txt

#### To install packages using requirements.tst files
copy requirements.txt file to virtualenv directory and run
pip install -r requiremets.txt

### To deactivate the environmet
# Goto virtualenv directory and run
deactivate



